Young Bode Bierdneau has been hailed a hero after risking his own life to save his dad's.

When his father John Taylor Bierdneau crashed his snowmobile in an isolated part of Lake Tahoe ski resort in California, breaking his leg, the nine-year-old jumped into action.

Bode tried digging his dad out of the snow as fast as he could, before riding for miles on his snowmobile without a cellphone or map to find help.

