'I was pretty nervous and it was just a lot of pressure on me I didn't know where to go and it was really hard,' Bode told ABC7.

'I was just really hoping he would be OK.'

The fourth grader from Marin County stayed calm, eventually stumbling on a tour group with an emergency radio. From there he led rescuers to his dad.

Bierdneau was flown to hospital with a broken leg, but family members say he is on the mend.

